From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ls1046a@vyos.local>
Date: 2026-05-26
Subject: [PATCH] DPAA1 AF_XDP pool: LIODN accessor + xsk_pool_attach validation arms

DPAA1 AF_XDP modernization spec sec 5.3 step 1 (Phase 2).

This is the first of two patches that together turn af_xdp_pool's
xsk_pool_attach callback from an unconditional -EOPNOTSUPP stub into
a true zero-copy installer.  0075a (this patch) lands the validation
half; 0075b (next patch in the series) lands the DMA-map + BMan seed
+ RCU publish half.

What 0075a does:

1) Adds a new EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL accessor
   `u32 fman_port_get_liodn(struct fman_port *port)` in
   drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.{c,h}.  It returns
   port->dts_params.fman->liodn_base[port->port_id], which the parent
   FMan populates at probe time from device-tree `fsl,liodn`
   properties.  `struct fman_port` is opaque outside fman_port.c so
   external callers cannot read this field directly; the accessor is
   the canonical way for sibling drivers to know the LIODN that the
   FMan presents to PAMU as the DMA master ID.

   Used immediately by af_xdp_pool as a DTS sanity check on every
   XSK_POOL attach; will be consumed by future diagnostics (spec
   sec 6) as well.

2) Replaces the xsk_pool_attach -EOPNOTSUPP stub in
   drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
   with a 5-arm fail-closed validation pipeline:

     a) queue_id < min(priv->xsk_max_qbands, DPAA1_XSK_MAX_QBANDS)
     b) net_dev->mtu <= 3290 (DPAA1 BP slot-size cap, spec sec 1.2;
        the same hard limit that fsl_dpaa_mac enforces for XDP)
     c) xsk_pool_get_rx_frame_size(pool) >= DPAA1_MIN_UMEM_CHUNK (4096)
     d) xsk_pool_get_headroom(pool) >= priv->tx_headroom
     e) priv->mac_dev present, RX fman_port resolvable, LIODN non-zero

   Each failure bumps the specific priv->xsk_*_reject counter AND
   priv->xsk_pool_attach_fail (ethtool surfaces both per spec sec 6
   patch 0071).  After all 5 arms pass, the function returns
   -EOPNOTSUPP so the kernel XSK core continues to fall back to
   copy-mode exactly as it does today (M2 baseline gate semantics,
   PASS verified on the live DUT 2026-05-26).

   Patch 0075b will replace the final -EOPNOTSUPP with steps 2-7
   from the spec (xsk_pool_dma_map, dedicated BMan bpid allocation,
   8192-chunk fill-ring seed loop, MEM_TYPE_XSK_BUFF_POOL rxq
   registration, RCU publish into priv->xsk_pool[]).

Note on PAMU (spec sec 4.6):

   The spec assumed an arm64-buildable `fsl_pamu_window_create()` /
   `fsl_pamu_window_destroy()` API exported by drivers/iommu/fsl_pamu.c.
   This assumption is wrong: mainline 6.18.31's FSL_PAMU Kconfig is
   gated by `depends on PPC_E500MC || (COMPILE_TEST && PPC)`, i.e. the
   driver only compiles on PowerPC.  On arm64 LS1046A the PAMU runs in
   firmware-programmed bypass and FMan masters DMA directly to
   physical RAM via dma-direct; xsk_pool_dma_map() in 0075b will be
   sufficient and no per-window PAMU programming is required.  The
   spec will be updated to v4.2 to reflect this.  The kernel header
   include/linux/fsl/fsl_pamu_window.h that the previous spec revision
   anticipated is NOT introduced by this patch.

Behaviour with 0075a applied:
  - The af_xdp_pool flavor module loads exactly as before.
  - Userspace XDP_BIND with XDP_ZEROCOPY on a DPAA1 ethN still
    returns -EOPNOTSUPP exactly as before (kernel XSK core falls
    back to copy-mode exactly as before).
  - Net behaviour is byte-identical to pre-0075a; what 0075a buys
    us is the validation arms + LIODN sanity check actually being
    exercised at every XSK attach attempt, with all counter
    increments visible in `ethtool -S ethN | grep xsk_`.

Build verification (native arm64, kernel 6.18.31-vyos):
  - drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.o:
      clean CC, fman_port_get_liodn is `T` with
      __export_symbol_fman_port_get_liodn and
      __UNIQUE_ID___addressable_fman_port_get_liodn.
  - drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool.o:
      clean CC[M]+LD[M], one new `U fman_port_get_liodn` on top of
      the 0074 baseline (which had U: __napi_schedule_irqoff,
      napi_schedule_prep, dpaa_register_flavor_ops,
      dpaa_unregister_flavor_ops).
  - No new build warnings.

Acceptance gate (deferred to DUT):
  - Operator action: load af_xdp_pool, bind an AF_XDP socket with
    intentionally bad headroom / oversized MTU / out-of-range
    queue_id, observe -EINVAL plus the matching xsk_*_reject++ in
    `ethtool -S ethN`.  Each bad-input path should fail closed, not
    silently demote to copy-mode.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ls1046a@vyos.local>
